# WHAT IT IS
#   memvid is the **single-file AI-memory CLI** — a typed local-
#   first RAG operator-tooling layer that turns a `.mv2` file
#   into a typed personal knowledge base.  Use cases:
#
#     • **Personal AI memory**          dump every personal
#                                       document (notes,
#                                       emails, screenshots,
#                                       PDFs, voice memos) into
#                                       a single typed `.mv2`,
#                                       then `memvid ask` to
#                                       recall typed
#                                       facts + summaries
#     • **Team knowledge base**         shared typed `.mv2` on
#                                       network-attached
#                                       storage with typed
#                                       crash-safe concurrent
#                                       writes (typed embedded
#                                       WAL + typed file-lock
#                                       coordination)
#     • **Compliance + audit trail**    typed `memvid audit`
#                                       emits typed provenance-
#                                       chained reports
#                                       suitable for typed
#                                       regulatory submissions
#     • **Time-aware research notes**   typed temporal-track
#                                       feature lets typed
#                                       `memvid when "last
#                                       Monday meeting"` resolve
#                                       typed natural-language
#                                       temporal phrases
#     • **Offline-capable knowledge
#       worker**                        once typed models are
#                                       cached locally via
#                                       typed `memvid models
#                                       download`, the entire
#                                       typed pipeline works
#                                       offline
#
#   Subcommand surface (clap-derive Subcommand enum;
#   feature-gated additions visible only when their typed
#   cargo feature is enabled at build time):
#
#     Memory file lifecycle:
#       • create <FILE>                 create a new `.mv2`
#                                       memory file
#       • open <FILE>                   inspect metadata +
#                                       manifests
#       • verify <FILE>                 integrity verification
#       • verify-single-file <FILE>     assert no auxiliary
#                                       files alongside
#       • doctor <FILE>                 repair + rebuild
#                                       indices
#       • stats <FILE>                  storage + index
#                                       utilization stats
#       • debug-segment <FILE>          dump raw vector segment
#                                       bytes
#       • process-queue <FILE>          process the typed
#                                       enrichment queue
#
#     Content ingest + edit:
#       • put <FILE>                    append a frame (file,
#                                       dir, URL) with optional
#                                       embeddings
#       • put-many <FILE>               batch ingest with pre-
#                                       computed embeddings
#                                       (feature: parallel_segments)
#       • api-fetch <FILE>              fetch remote content +
#                                       ingest
